Bruce Cook has been warned by police that he could face serious charges if he doesn't take down his 'offensive' hay bale structure . 
  The sculpture depicts the intimacy between a cow and a bull out the front of his property at Lake Charm in northwest Victoria . 
  Mr Cook says police told him to take down the structure after they received a complaint . 
  He says he put it up on Good Friday as 'a bit of fun' The 59-year-old says he could be charged with 'publishing pornographic images'